%N A394389 The number of squares visited by a (1,2)-darter moving on a square-spiral numbered board, starting from square n, and always moving to the lowest available unvisited square that can be reached without crossing a square that has been previously visited  (Cf. A394387).
%C A394389 The first path to have the longest length before being trapped after the first step to a larger square than the previous one is for start square 71, which visits 3 squares moving toward the central 1 square before visiting a further 141 squares before being trapped. See the attached image.
%C A394389 The shortest path is that of 13 visited squares when starting from square 11. See the image in A394388.
%C A394389 See A394387 for more information, and A394388 for the final square when starting from square n.
%H A394389 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394389/b394389.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394389 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394389/a394389.png">Image of the path for a(71) = 144</a>. The start and end squares are colored green and red respectively, while the 8 squares around the final square that the darter is blocked from moving to are colored blue.
%e A394389 a(1) = 88. See A394387.
%e A394389 a(11) = 13. See A394388.
%e A394389 a(71) = 144. See the attached image.
%Y A394389 Cf. A394387, A394388 (end squares), A316667, A394363, A336208, A383185.
%K A394389 nonn,walk,new
%O A394389 1,1
